  "text": "Overall, most studies suggested bioequivalence of brand and generic AEDs. This result was also in keeping with a meta-analysis which concluded that if only the highest level of evidence is considered, there is no significant difference in terms of seizure control, whether or not the patient is taking brand or generic products. [CITATION_1] A UK pharmacovigilance body, the Medicine and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency, issued guidelines regarding the use of generic products in 2013 and specifically divided AEDs into three categories, each of which had specific recommendations regarding the switching of brand to generic products (Appendix).",
